body:
Hello.

I've been around for 2 years however I didn't play for about a year in the middle. Former Mod and Dev on Avalanche. I upload videos on the youtube account: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCRYi0KSqwR8fbwCDHHen2Ug. I'm current part of Big Dango Family on OCN and currently I am on Apollo here, on Avicus. I have been part of Bad Company and Team Lightning here and numerous teams such as Ambush, EffV, Storm, VnD and Escalate; I played HCF on Shotbow for 15 maps (13-28) however only actively for the first 7. 

I returned to Avicus after my IRL friend (Notal) asked me to make a team with him. I didn't really want to recruit one myself seeing as I didn't know anyone so I would be useless, however I would lead in game and be more active when we had a base roster. However, I joined BC after Notal approached me. I thought I was a leader from the start because of that and that is why my attitude was so bad. I have more of a firm leading style which Avicus players are not used to. Yes, I will answer questions about why I was kicked.

I consider myself a very good objective player who is also a good tactician. My comms have improved over time and I believe I have changed after I was kicked. I am sorry for my past attitude, I didn't realise it was that bad until I was kicked.

For the maps, I'm not sure. I just got bored one day and started something with Jive and Robin. That map never got anywhere and got abandoned. Then, Robin asked for some feedback on his map, that he said he was about to abandon. I saw potential in it and I took it over. Next, Sli asked me if Barney and I wanted to be added to the trello so we could judge maps, and I said yea, I'll sort it out later. However, later that day BmB got Jr. MapDev and I thought it was for both of us because of the past offer ROFL so I asked for it as well.

Best experience on Avicus was probably beating Berzerk in the Semis.

I really like you however I don't really know a lot about you. Because you have no mic, I don't really know you if that makes sense. I think that you're a quite capable offender however when I played for Apollo, I didn't see much from you as I took your position and I think you were going through a bad patch at that point, or I couldn't hear you to know what you were doing.
